{"key":"post-10132704","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10132704</id>\n<content>If you make the substrate over 2&quot; thick, it won't fruit.&amp;nbsp; Pan cyans like a thin cow or horse manure substrate.&amp;nbsp; I found that 1 1/2&quot; depth is about right.&amp;nbsp; Too many people try to treat them like cubes and get nothing for their effort.&amp;nbsp; Keep the peat/verm casing layer to 1/4&quot; thickness.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10132785</next>\n<prev>10132598</prev>\n<first>10132025</first>\n<last>10200487</last>\n<when>1239242851</when>\n<utime>04/09/09 05:07 AM</utime>\n</post>"}